member.name: T:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.Data.ResultTable
member.summary: Contains a single result table. The table is returned as an array of rows that contain the values for the cells of the table. Depending on the metric or dimension, the cell can contain a string (video ID, country code) or a number (number of views or number of likes).

member.name: P:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.Data.ResultTable.ColumnHeaders
member.summary: Contains information about the columns returned in the "rows" fields. The order of the elements matches the order of the corresponding columns in "rows" field.

member.name: P:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.Data.ResultTable.Kind
member.summary: Identifier used to mark the structure as a result table.

member.name: P:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.Data.ResultTable.Rows
member.summary: Contains all rows of the result table. Each row contains an array with the values for the columns. The order matches the order of the column information provided in the "columnHeaders" field. If no data is available for the given query, the "rows" element will be omitted from the response. The response for a query with the day dimension will not contain rows for the most recent days.

member.name: P:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.Data.ResultTable.ColumnHeadersData.ColumnType
member.summary: The type of the column (DIMENSION, METRIC).

member.name: P:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.Data.ResultTable.ColumnHeadersData.DataType
member.summary: Type of the data in the column (STRING, INTEGER, FLOAT).

member.name: P:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.Data.ResultTable.ColumnHeadersData.Name
member.summary: The name of the dimension or metric.

member.name: M:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.ReportsResource.Query(System.String,System.String,System.String,System.String)
member.summary: Retrieve your YouTube Analytics reports.
member.param: Required - Must match pattern [a-zA-Z]+==[a-zA-Z0-9_+-]+ - Unique channel or content owner ID for retrieving YouTube Analytics data. Either channel==C or contentOwner==O where 'C' is the encrypted channel ID and 'O' is the content owner name.
start-date - Required - Must match pattern [0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2} - Start date for fetching YouTube Analytics data. All requests should specify a start date formatted as YYYY-MM-DD.
end-date - Required - Must match pattern [0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2} - End date for fetching YouTube Analytics data. All requests should specify an end date formatted as YYYY-MM-DD.
Required - Must match pattern [0-9a-zA-Z,]+ - A comma-separated list of YouTube Analytics metrics. E.g., 'views' or 'likes,dislikes'

member.name: P:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.ReportsResource.QueryRequest.EndDate

member.name: P:Google.Apis.YoutubeAnalytics.v1beta1.ReportsResource.QueryRequest.Filters
member.summary: A list of dimension filters to be applied to YouTube Analytics data. Multiple filters can be joined together with the ';' character. The returned result table will satisfy both filters. E.g., video==dMH0bHeiRNg;country==IT will restrict the returned stats to the given video and the country Italy.

member.summary: Unique channel or content owner ID for retrieving YouTube Analytics data. Either channel==C or contentOwner==O where 'C' is the encrypted channel ID and 'O' is the content owner name.
